 21  /-- Countable sets
 22  
 23  A set is countable if there exists an encoding of the set into the natural numbers.
 24  An encoding is an injection with a partial inverse, which can be viewed as a
 25  constructive analogue of countability. (For the most part, theorems about
 26  `countable` will be classical and `encodable` will be constructive.)
 27  -/
 28  def countable (s : set α) : Prop := nonempty (encodable s)
